=== Palpitations
<subsec:palpitations>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Awareness of heartbeat (racing, pounding, or irregular)
    - Tachycardia (elevated heart rate) at rest or with minimal activity
    - Premature ventricular contractions (PVCs) or atrial ectopy
    - Palpitations triggered by position changes, exertion, or stress
    - Often benign but distressing

*Mechanism.*
Palpitations reflect autonomic dysfunction, orthostatic intolerance, and potential cardiac preload failure. The heart races in an attempt to compensate for inadequate venous return and reduced stroke volume.
